verses.text_plain: My son, attend unto my wisdom, and bow thine ear to my understanding:
verses.verse_html: 1My son, attend unto my wisdom, and bow thine ear to my understanding:

verses.text_plain: That thou mayest regard discretion, and that thy lips may keep knowledge.
verses.verse_html: 2That thou mayest regard discretion, and that thy lips may keep knowledge.

verses.text_plain: For the lips of a strange woman drop as an honeycomb, and her mouth is smoother than oil:
verses.verse_html:
3For the lips of a strange woman drop as an honeycomb, and her mouth is smoother than oil: ▼
▼ mouth: Heb. palate

verses.text_plain: But her end is bitter as wormwood, sharp as a twoedged sword.
verses.verse_html: 4But her end is bitter as wormwood, sharp as a twoedged sword.

verses.text_plain: Her feet go down to death; her steps take hold on hell.
verses.verse_html: 5Her feet go down to death; her steps take hold on hell.

verses.text_plain: Lest thou shouldest ponder the path of life, her ways are moveable, that thou canst not know them.
verses.verse_html: 6Lest thou shouldest ponder the path of life, her ways are moveable, that thou canst not know them.

verses.text_plain: Hear me now therefore, O ye children, and depart not from the words of my mouth.
verses.verse_html: 7Hear me now therefore, O ye children, and depart not from the words of my mouth.

tokens.text: me now therefore, O ye children

verses.text_plain: Remove thy way far from her, and come not nigh the door of her house:
verses.verse_html: 8Remove thy way far from her, and come not nigh the door of her house:

tokens.text: from her, and come not nigh

verses.text_plain: Lest thou give thine honour unto others, and thy years unto the cruel:
verses.verse_html: 9Lest thou give thine honour unto others, and thy years unto the cruel:

verses.text_plain: Lest strangers be filled with thy wealth; and thy labours be in the house of a stranger;
verses.verse_html:
10Lest strangers be filled with thy wealth; and thy labours be in the house of a stranger; ▼
▼ thy wealth: Heb. thy strength

footnotes.body_html: ▼ thy wealth: Heb. thy strength

verses.text_plain: And thou mourn at the last, when thy flesh and thy body are consumed,
verses.verse_html: 11And thou mourn at the last, when thy flesh and thy body are consumed,

verses.text_plain: And say, How have I hated instruction, and my heart despised reproof;
verses.verse_html: 12And say, How have I hated instruction, and my heart despised reproof;

verses.text_plain: And have not obeyed the voice of my teachers, nor inclined mine ear to them that instructed me!
verses.verse_html: 13And have not obeyed the voice of my teachers, nor inclined mine ear to them that instructed me!

verses.text_plain: I was almost in all evil in the midst of the congregation and assembly.
verses.verse_html: 14I was almost in all evil in the midst of the congregation and assembly.

verses.text_plain: Drink waters out of thine own cistern, and running waters out of thine own well.
verses.verse_html: 15Drink waters out of thine own cistern, and running waters out of thine own well.

verses.text_plain: Let thy fountains be dispersed abroad, and rivers of waters in the streets.
verses.verse_html: 16Let thy fountains be dispersed abroad, and rivers of waters in the streets.

verses.text_plain: Let them be only thine own, and not strangers’ with thee.
verses.verse_html: 17Let them be only thine own, and not strangers’ with thee.

tokens.text: Let them be only thine own, and not strangers’

verses.text_plain: Let thy fountain be blessed: and rejoice with the wife of thy youth.
verses.verse_html: 18Let thy fountain be blessed: and rejoice with the wife of thy youth.

verses.text_plain: Let her be as the loving hind and pleasant roe; let her breasts satisfy thee at all times; and be thou ravished always with her love.
verses.verse_html:
19Let her be as the loving hind and pleasant roe; let her breasts satisfy thee at all times; and be thou ravished always with her love. ▼
▼ satisfy…: Heb. water thee
 , ▼
▼ be thou…: Heb. err thou always in her love

footnotes.body_html: ▼ satisfy…: Heb. water thee

footnotes.body_text: ▼ be thou…: Heb. err thou always in her love
footnotes.body_html: ▼ be thou…: Heb. err thou always in her love

verses.text_plain: And why wilt thou, my son, be ravished with a strange woman, and embrace the bosom of a stranger?
verses.verse_html: 20And why wilt thou, my son, be ravished with a strange woman, and embrace the bosom of a stranger?

tokens.text: And why wilt thou, my son

verses.text_plain: For the ways of man are before the eyes of the Lord, and he pondereth all his goings.
verses.verse_html: 21For the ways of man are before the eyes of the Lord, and he pondereth all his goings.

verses.text_plain: His own iniquities shall take the wicked himself, and he shall be holden with the cords of his sins.
verses.verse_html:
22His own iniquities shall take the wicked himself, and he shall be holden with the cords of his sins. ▼
▼ sins: Heb. sin

tokens.text: himself, and he shall be holden

verses.text_plain: He shall die without instruction; and in the greatness of his folly he shall go astray.
verses.verse_html: 23He shall die without instruction; and in the greatness of his folly he shall go astray.
